column7: REDWOOD CITY, Calif., July 5, 2017 /PRNewswire/ -- Nevro Corp. (NVRO), a global medical device company that is providing innovative evidence-based solutions for the treatment of chronic pain, today announced its preliminary unaudited revenue for the second quarter ended June 30, 2017.  The company announced that preliminary unaudited second quarter worldwide revenue is expected to be in the range of $77.5 to $78.0 million, compared to $55.4 million in the second quarter of 2016.  The company expects worldwide revenue for the full year 2017 to be in the range of $310.0 to $320.0 million.

TOTAL_PAGES: 1: Neurosurgery Selects the SENZA-RCT 24-Month Outcomes Publication as the Top Pain Paper of the Year
column7: REDWOOD CITY, Calif., June 15, 2017 /PRNewswire/ -- Nevro Corp. (NVRO), a global medical device company that is providing innovative evidence-based solutions for the treatment of chronic pain, today announced that Neurosurgery, the official journal of the Congress of Neurological Surgeons (CNS), selected the SENZA-RCT 24-month outcomes publication as the journal's Top Pain Paper of the Year.  The SENZA-RCT is a groundbreaking pivotal study that was both the largest prospective randomized clinical trial ever conducted to assess the treatment of chronic back and leg pain, and the first to evaluate comparative effectiveness of spinal cord stimulation (SCS) therapies.  Each paper was subject to a rigorous review process with the journal's editorial board, beginning with initial selection from the entire pool of papers published between June 2016 and June 2017.  "The CNS is committed to providing relevant and informative science to our members.
